This paper deals with the problem of skyline queries, which is a common topic in the database community. Specifically, it extends the k-dominant skyline queries to the join paradigm, which involves combining multiple relations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DB (database) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and data structures for efficient computation of skyline queries, which are common topics in the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of aggregated values in skyline queries, which is a topic in the cs.IR (information retrieval) sub-category. The use of preferences and optimization in skyline queries suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.AI (artificial intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimization and efficiency techniques, which are common topics in the cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) sub-category.
